the Freudian concept of denial

00:16:02.780 --> 00:16:08.190
as technologies of effective denial
of the menstrual body traces.

00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:11.650
The second major tactic
was the following.

00:16:11.650 --> 00:16:16.790
The industrial patent tampons
were disseminated alongside a new

00:16:16.790 --> 00:16:21.230
legitimized way of thinking
and talking about menstruation,

00:16:21.230 --> 00:16:24.010
which was supported by the
biomedical modern knowledge.

00:16:24.010 --> 00:16:30.460
This new way of doing, thinking
and talking about menstruation

00:16:30.460 --> 00:16:35.270
that this industry disseminated
transnationally displaced gradually

00:16:35.270 --> 00:16:38.870
the traditional knowledge
of women about menstruation.

00:16:38.870 --> 00:16:45.080
The work of [inaudible] and
Elizabeth Kisling were crucial

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:50.150
to understand what
happened in the US.

